Package aima.core.util.datastructure

Interface Summary
Queue<E> Artificial Intelligence A Modern Approach (3rd Edition): pg 79.

The operations on a queue are as follows:
EMPTY?(queue) returns true only if there are no elements in the queue POP(queue) removes teh first element of the queue and returns it. INSERT(element, queue) inserts and element and returns the resulting queue. Note: This extends the java.util.Queue collections interface in order to take advantage of pre-existing implementations.
